---
description: shadcn/ui, Tailwind, and component conventions
globs: ["src/components/**/*.ts", "src/components/**/*.tsx", "src/app/**/*.tsx", "src/app/globals.css"]
alwaysApply: false
---

UI rules:

- Use shadcn/ui patterns for reusable primitives.
- Keep components composable and focused.
- Prefer semantic HTML first, utility classes second.
- Use `cn()` for class composition.
- Do not create giant multi-purpose components.
- Keep visual variants in CVA where it improves reuse.
- Preserve focus styles and accessible names.
- Prefer design-token variables over hardcoded one-off values.
- Keep loading, empty, error, and success states visible in the UI.
